{
  "name": "RPlog_The_Ambassador_s_New_Clothes",
  "title": "Mother, Daughter, and a Hidden Comlink",
  "summary": "Confined to lavish upgraded quarters aboard the V2SD Nemesis as captives of Lord Thel, the ambassador Ambrosia Delgard and her estranged Imperial-raised daughter, the young Doctor Kovani, share a tense, halting reconciliation. Over a smuggled pastry, Ambrosia warns Kovani to be ready to follow her lead should the Republic mount a rescue, and Kovani secretly presses a short-range comlink into her mother's hand, hoping to patch into the flagship's communications to save her own Imperial friends. Ambrosia at last tells Kovani the full truth of her origins: conceived when Ambrosia was an Imperial pleasure-slave by the official Tyruni, taken away at birth and presumed dead, with Ambrosia later discarded and surviving a prison-transport crash to become a Republic diplomat. When Kovani tries to research her father through the terminal, ISB security locks every database and finally disables the unit, and she breaks her hand punching the screen in fury. Ambrosia tends the injury and calls a stormtrooper escort to take Kovani to the medical bay, using the staged commotion to conceal the comlink on her person as she settles in to await a technician and a change of clothes.",
